main event: Two cigar-shaped objects traveling at high speed were observed in Goodlettsville, Tennessee on December 8, 1961.
interesting points: The objects were detected by ground radar and had unusual flight characteristics., The sighting lasted between 5 to 15 seconds., The objects disappeared instantaneously after being seen., The witness was able to estimate they were 1 to 1.5 miles away., The sighting was reported to the U.S. Air Force but was later attributed to moonlit contrails.
witness description: One male witness aged 28 with 2 years of I.T. experience.
